&lt;h2 id="the-story-of-robert-berry-pac"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Story of Robert Berry (PAC)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a class="anchor" href="#the-story-of-robert-berry-pac"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Robert Berry (PAC)&lt;/strong&gt; of South Norfolk County, Virginia, married &lt;strong&gt;Mary Williamson&lt;/strong&gt; and established a home in &lt;strong&gt;Princess Anne County, Virginia&lt;/strong&gt;, which is now known as Virginia Beach, Virginia. Robert and Mary had two sons. The oldest was Richard Berry and the baby was &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://berrytree.org/ancestors/robert-berry-oc/"&gt;Robert Berry &amp;ldquo;Orange County, NC&amp;rdquo; (OC)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; who was born about 1729. Robert Berry (PAC) wrote his will in 1730 and died shortly after Robert Berry (Orange County, NC) was born. &lt;!-- UNSOURCED --&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>William Clarence Berry NC, ALA, TX</title><link>https://berrytree.org/ancestors/william-clarence-berry-nc/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://berrytree.org/ancestors/william-clarence-berry-nc/</guid><description>&lt;div class="ancestor-page"&gt;

