&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gen 1&lt;/strong&gt; Robert Berry × Mary Williamson — Princess Anne County, Virginia&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gen 2&lt;/strong&gt; Robert Berry × Elizabeth Cate — Orange County, North Carolina&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gen 3&lt;/strong&gt; Joshua Berry × Nancy Ellison — Orange County, North Carolina&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;James Berry was born in 1800 in Orange County, North Carolina. &lt;!-- UNSOURCED --&gt;
James Berry and Mary Parker were married in North Carolina about 1829. &lt;!-- UNSOURCED --&gt; Their first three daughters were born in North Carolina. The oldest daughter, Nancy, was born in 1830. The youngest daughter, Delila, was born in North Carolina in 1836 and was 14 years old in the 1850 Smith County, Tennessee census. The oldest child born in Tennessee was, Martha, who was 11 years old in 1850.
This means James and Mary were in North Carolina in 1836 and in Tennessee in 1839.
I have no absolute proof that the James Berry on this page is related to us but all the facts indicate he was..
&lt;figure class="img-float img-float-none"&gt;
 &lt;img src="https://berrytree.org/images/roberttojoshua.jpg" alt="roberttojoshua" /&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;strong&gt;Robert Berry&amp;rsquo;s Deed to Joshua Berry with James Berry as a witness. Dated February 24 1811 (Orange County Deed Book 14 Page 57)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Land Grant to Robert Berry Jr. by President Monroe</title><link>https://berrytree.org/documents/land-grant-to-robert-berry-jr/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://berrytree.org/documents/land-grant-to-robert-berry-jr/</guid><description>&lt;div class="info-banner" role="banner"&gt;
 &lt;p class="info-banner-title"&gt;Land Grant to Robert Berry Jr.&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;p class="info-banner-subtitle"&gt;President Monroe&amp;#39;s land grant certificate for Robert Berry Jr. in Alabama.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This land grant certificate was issued by President Monroe to Robert Berry Jr. for property in Alabama.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class="img-float img-float-none"&gt;
 &lt;img src="https://berrytree.org/images/numberblandgrantcertificateala1824.jpg" alt="Land Grant Certificate to Robert Berry Jr. issued by President Monroe, Alabama 1824" /&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;</description></item><item><title>Proof Page</title><link>https://berrytree.org/ancestors/proofpage/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://berrytree.org/ancestors/proofpage/</guid><description>&lt;div class="info-banner" role="banner"&gt;
 &lt;p class="info-banner-title"&gt;Proof of the Berry-Williamson Connection&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;p class="info-banner-subtitle"&gt;Evidence linking Robert Berry of Orange County, NC, to Princess Anne County, Virginia, through the Williamson and Kempe families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This page assembles the documentary evidence connecting Robert Berry of Orange County, NC, to Princess Anne County, Virginia, through shared surnames, tax lists, and land records.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Robert C. Berry NC Ala</title><link>https://berrytree.org/ancestors/robert-c-berry-alabama/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://berrytree.org/ancestors/robert-c-berry-alabama/</guid><description>&lt;div class="ancestor-page"&gt;

